- Business: Apply this label if the passage mainly concerns finance, company performance, the stock market, economics, business management, mergers/acquisitions, or commercial and industry developments.

- Sci/Tech (Science/Technology): Use this label if the news is primarily about scientific research, technology products or innovations, new gadgets, electronics, computers, or developments in science and technology. Prioritize Sci/Tech if the text focuses on the advancement, creation, or introduction of technology or scientific discoveries, even if those have business implications (for example, news about new digital storage systems or software should be labeled Sci/Tech if the technological or scientific element is primary).

